Why This Works

The greedy decision is:

Whenever a larger digit appears before a smaller digit, remove the larger digit if you still have removals left (k > 0).

This always makes the number smaller from the most significant position, which has the greatest impact on the final value.

Interview Pattern

Whenever you see:

Remove digits
Build the smallest/largest number
Compare adjacent digits
Greedy removal

Think:

Monotonic Stack + Greedy

This is one of the most common patterns in stack-based interview questions and is worth mastering before moving on to harder greedy problems.
